<paragraph blockId="23.[151,1437,153,251]" pageId="23" pageNumber="540">
The ventral margin of the style of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Osborn. Detailed" authorityYear="1938" box="[581,687,153,179]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Scaroidana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="540" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavida">
<emphasis box="[581,687,153,179]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="540">S. flavida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[701,806,153,179]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Scaroidana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="540" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fulvula">
<emphasis box="[701,806,153,179]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="540">S. fulvula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="DeLong" authorityYear="1982" box="[860,980,153,179]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Scaroidana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="540" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="blockeri">
<emphasis box="[860,980,153,179]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="540">S. blockeri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are serrated and, second 
<bibRefCitation author="Kramer, J. P." box="[1262,1431,153,180]" pageId="23" pageNumber="540" pagination="37 - 50" refId="ref19536" refString="Kramer, J. P. (1963) A key to the New World genera of Iassinae with reviews of Scaroidana and Pachyopsis (Homoptera: Cicadellidae). Bulletin of the Brooklyn Entomological Society, 58 (2 / 3), 37 - 50." type="journal article" year="1963">Kramer (1963)</bibRefCitation>
, in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kramer" authorityYear="1963" box="[179,282,189,215]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Scaroidana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="540" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="xouthe">
<emphasis box="[179,282,189,215]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="540">S. xouthe</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the ventral margin is not serrated. In 
<taxonomicName box="[697,788,189,215]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Scaroidana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="540" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spura">
<emphasis box="[697,788,189,215]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="540">S. spura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
this character was not mentioned in the description of this species but, according to the illustration (
<bibRefCitation author="Freytag, P. H." box="[612,779,225,251]" pageId="23" pageNumber="540" pagination="499 - 501" refId="ref19160" refString="Freytag, P. H. (2018 b) A New Species of Scaroidana (Hemiptera: Cicadellidae: Iassinae) from Colombia. Entomological news, 127 (5), 499 - 501. https: // doi. org / 10.3157 / 021.127.0515" type="journal article" year="2018">Freytag 2018b</bibRefCitation>
, fig. 4), the style is apparently not serrated as in 
<emphasis box="[1322,1432,225,251]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="540">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kramer" authorityYear="1963" box="[1322,1428,225,251]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Scaroidana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="540" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="xouthe">S. xouthe</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
